    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Financial Analyst to strengthen our Vadodara-based team.\n\nAbout Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners:\nBajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vadodara, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners!",
